    <text id="R151256T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Robert E. Lee writes General John Floyd in August, 1861, to discuss regiments
                    expected to arrive in Staunton.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Gen. JOHN B. FLOYD,<lb/> Cmdg. Army of Kanawha, Camp
                        Gauley, west of Lewisburg, Va.:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1861-08-27">August 27, 1861.</date>
                        <name type="place">Valley Mountain,</name><name type="location">HDQRS.,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>GEN.:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Since my letter of yesterday I have heard that the Thirtieth Georgia Regt. was
                    expected at Staunton, and have directed that it be ordered to join your command.
                    This, with the Fourteen Regt. North Carolina Volunteers, which you were advised
                    was on its way to Lewisburg, will give you two well-appointed regiments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>I have the honor to be, your obedient servant,</salute>
                    <signed>R. E. LEE,<lb/> Gen., Cmdg.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
